##On New Year's Eve in Wuhan, I observed by myself at home

Micro-signal Zairenjian11

Features, with a calm narrative against the cold | phoenix network produced in the human studio

The following article is from the Earth's Youth Almanac, the author of Diqing

The alternative to being young

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
"Wuhan may seem like a isolated city in the map of China at the moment, but in fact there are countless isolated cities within the Jericho, with thousands of former families who have locked themselves in their homes, seemingly at peace but with a tight thread in their hearts, " wrote one respondent, Zhang Heng.

We interviewed five young people who had spent the Lunar New Year holiday in Wuhan and talked about their recent experiences, including those who had returned to Wuhan from Beijing, Shanghai and other places, as well as Wuhan natives who had never left.

On the surface, it's peaceful,

But there's a thread tightening around my heart

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Daddy grows vegetables at home

Zhang Heng (not his real name) , 24-year-old cafe owner, lives in Jiangxia District

I ran a coffee shop in Shanghai with a friend, and on December 30 I saw the circular circulating on the Internet about the south China Seafood Market. My immediate reaction was to look for information right away, and I found it seemed to be true, i sent it to my parents in Wuhan. They didn't know it yet.

Later, more and more news about pneumonia, to January 20, the people around me are urging me not to go home for the New Year, I also think it was nothing, everyone was very afraid, but I this Wuhan people are not afraid.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Mama's cooking

I thought, only the New Year to have time to go back to see mom and dad, do not go back now, do not know when to wait. There are a lot of Bacon at home waiting for me, the suitcase has been wrapped for my parents Hongbao. Everyone advised me not to go back, I really do not want not to go back, I told them all right, so in the afternoon of January 22 arrived in Wuhan.

Out of the subway, I saw my parents waiting for me in the subway entrance, they did not wear a mask, I immediately criticized them, said the heart is too big, my parents joke that it is all right, a short while back home. Along the way I told my parents a lot of information about this pneumonia, infection data now, how to choose masks, how to wear, how to prevent and so on.

As is the custom in past years, when I came back, my family's itinerary was full, so I was a little worried. Sure enough, my mom told me I was going to grandma's tomorrow. The next morning, I opened my mobile phone to see the city of Wuhan "closed" message, the airport railway station closed channels, public transport is suspended. Before going out, I gave the mask I brought back from Shanghai to my parents and told them to wear it.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
My father began to carve the string of hands years ago

Not far from Grandma's house, we decided to take a taxi. There were no pedestrians on the street, only a few cars running. It was not an easy day to get a taxi. At ten o'clock in the morning, when we got a taxi, we were already in sixth place. We waited about half an hour before getting on the bus. Mom and dad sat in the back, I sat in the passenger seat, did not sit firmly, the driver said directly, "to raise the price. ".

I did not realize for a moment, did not think in the platform taxi, the driver is so bold. I was very surprised and said: "You still raise the price? You are not afraid I complain you? "

The driver is more just, "I have come out to drive Didi, I am afraid you complain? " The parents sit in the back, I also not good to continue to argue with the driver, thought originally also not easy, in case he did not see us off. I said impatiently, "okay, go, go, go. "

All four of us, including the driver, were wearing masks. As we drove for a while, I noticed that my father had quietly opened the window a little, and the cold wind was blowing in.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
At thirty, mother is preparing to cook fish in the kitchen.

Twenty-nine, at noon, at my grandmother's home, we and uncle, uncle and two, barely had a dinner. Because of some friction between relatives, we just "body" in this table.

No one opened their mouths. No one talked about work, school, or love. Only grandpa talked about pneumonia he saw on TV today. I actually had a rather cheery New Year's Eve dinner. We got home before five o'clock that afternoon.

New Year's Eve dinner

On New Year's Eve, parents'perceptions of pneumonia changed, perhaps because the city was closed so they realized how serious the epidemic was. New Year's Eve, parents busy all afternoon, the three of us eat more than five o'clock.

The Spring Festival gala began. We Sat on the SOFA, laughing and making fun of each other. Our parents were doing two things in between the programs that nobody was interested in. One thing is in a variety of social networking platforms to grab red envelopes, cards and so on, the other thing is that parents have been reading all kinds of pneumonia articles and videos.

I heard my father brush to a video, perhaps the medical staff is too much pressure, video of a female doctor sent a desperate narrative, saying "I can not hold on, too tired, do not expect anyone to save you" and so on. Dad looked at the end of the act as if nothing had happened, looked up to see the Spring Festival gala.

At that moment, I even felt that mom and dad had been given too much information about the outbreak, which in a way exacerbated their anxiety, not to mention their ability to tell if it was true or not.

In this epidemic-ridden New Year's Eve festival, we are trying to keep calm, to teach themselves to be strong and optimistic. But who knows how much longer we can hold out under that smile.

This is my lucky year. Dad gave me a golden mouse.

After the closure of the city all Wuhan people have become more cautious, the city seems to have a pair of hands to all Wuhan People's heads down, let us bow to admit fault. But maybe we should.

Going home these days, although I also sent out a friend's circle to tell everyone that I was in Wuhan, when I met some friends on Wechat who I didn't know very well and asked me privately whether I was in Wuhan, I was all a little worried, thinking that they were coming to join the fun, i haven't responded to any of their texts.

Wuhan may seem like a lonely city in the map of China at the moment, but in fact there are countless lonely cities within the city of Jericho, thousands of former families who have locked themselves in their homes, seemingly at peace with themselves, but there's a thread tightening around my heart.

I'm afraid that when I go back to Shanghai, people will keep their distance from me because I'm from Wuhan. By the way, I don't know when I can leave Wuhan. Expect more good news, the epidemic is under control, the cure is out, the vaccine is ready.

I had a cold. I was at home playing video games and stroking my cat

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The cold medicine I took

Shuyao is a 25-year-old private equity researcher who lives in Wuchang District

I am a Wuhan native working in Hangzhou and currently working as a private equity researcher in a financial company. It used to be that we went back to Hubei every year for the New Year, and this year is no exception.

Before returning to Wuhan, I caught a cold, saw a doctor in Hangzhou, also prescribed medicine, but I always did not take medicine on time, have been repeatedly cold. At first, I didn't care too much. The report was not as infectious as SARS, and the mortality rate was not high. Moreover, most of the death cases showed at that time were from other diseases. So I went home directly.

Later gradually spread to Fengcheng, oneself also a little nervous, it seems to be much more serious than at first thought. Plans to return to Red Cliff, an hour and a half's drive from Wuhan, were cancelled.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
I stayed at home all the time, didn't go out, didn't do any preparation when I came back, my family had all the supplies, vegetables, meat, water, and sanitary articles in place. I haven't been getting over my cold, which is scary, because I'm starting to wonder if it's turned into pneumonia.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
In the afternoon of the Year of thirty, I asked a friend to play an online game.

For Fear of cross-infection in the hospital in Wuhan, did not go to the hospital. At home with some friends to play destiny 2 on Steam, and Jack off to cat, and edamame, the orange cat he's had for three years.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
I make dumplings with my mother

In the past, when I was a child, I went back to my hometown for the Spring Festival gala, and my family gathered around a charcoal fire to keep warm, chat and watch the New Year. Later, my grandparents also moved to the city. In the New Year, everyone gathered at home for a meal together, the Spring Festival gala is not so good either. This is the loss of only know how to treasure? After the closure of the city, but feel the value of the New Year, so quite cherish these days, can spend more time at home with my mother and edamame.

Although sick will be more worried, but such a simple new year, I still feel pretty good. Because I'm a bit of a nerd myself, and I don't like parties and crowds.

On New Year's Eve, I was at home alone observing myself

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Delta 21, I'm going out with a mask on.

She's a 25-year-old dance teacher from Jianghan District

I'm a native of Wuhan and a local dance teacher, and my usual class is in the office building next to the Hankou Railway Station. I haven't left the House since I felt it was serious. I've been home.

From last December to early January this year, the basic in the dance class, just heard the news of COVID-19, in fact, did not take it too seriously. At that time can see the news is to tell everyone not to worry, there is no sign of human-to-human transmission. Including the Hankou Railway Station. I don't see any protection. I didn't pay much attention, and the pace of my life wasn't affected at all.

As far as Fengcheng, during this period, more and more information received, more unofficial, some groups in Wuhan, or survival is not high micro-blog news. It wasn't until the official announcement of the siege came out that I immediately panicked and realized how serious it was.

The news was posted at 2 am on the 23rd. I got up at 3 am and rushed to stock up on the APP, buying some fast food and well stocked fruits and vegetables. Disinfectant has been robbed, can only the next day armed to go out to find, but also to go out to spend masks and disinfectant, home inventory has been bottomed out.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The family dog

Because the incubation period of the epidemic up to more than 10 days, I frequent high-risk areas, so I canceled all the parties, my parents to send me vegetables were also discouraged by me. I feel like I have a pretty good chance of catching it, and I've been watching myself at home lately.

This outbreak is GonNa have an impact on our work, but we're not thinking about it right now. There's been so much contact in high-risk areas, it's hard to feel safe.

At first I would go out to walk the dog, then only in the community to walk the dog, then open the door to let the dog in the corridor two steps, now do not dare to open the door. Every day at home to turn on the TV to watch the play, to tell the truth, also can not see, in addition to eating and sleeping, is constantly refreshing the news, watching the news, brushing, crying for a while, continue to brush after crying.

Meals on wheels at home

But at this point, appetite is still very good, want to eat hot dry noodles want to eat hot pot, appetite is the evidence of health it. Of course, each meal dare not eat too much, as little as possible but balanced nutrition.

There is a sense of pessimism about the information available, a sense of waiting for a "hero. " But in fact, if things had been well monitored and managed in the early stages, we might not have expected a "hero" as much as we do now.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Hot Pot on New Year's Eve

On New Year's Eve, I turned on the TV to show the Spring Festival gala, and prepared a hot pot, but the Spring Festival gala is not to see into, long-distance video chat with friends. Using his mobile phone to brush a self-proclaimed "know the internal system of the people, " the micro-blog, finally see a little bit of hope.

The original plan is to reunite with my family, and like people shopping, but the reality is only a person at home on New Year's Eve, this day is also my recent psychological state of the worst day.

Spend the "special" New Year with each other

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
I've got window coverings at home

Freezing point, 25-year-old analyst, lives in Hanyang District

I lived in Xiangyang, Hubei Province, until I was 18, then moved to Beijing to study and now works as an analyst for a start-up in Beijing. My parents moved to Wuhan a few years ago, so I go back to Wuhan every year for Chinese New Year.

I booked my ticket back to Wuhan as early as possible. On New Year's Eve, the world is still peaceful. All I can think about is the stress of only taking one day off this week, because I will be home next week for the New Year, and I still have a lot to do.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
There's food in the fridge at home

On the 19th, some disturbing news began to spread. Everyone is talking about Wuhan Pneumonia, some people send messages to ask me, New Year still go home. At that time I did not take it seriously, I said no matter what, home or to go back.

When I woke up the next morning, it was all about the pneumonia outbreak in Wuhan. From this day on, all the wechat groups like an explosion, all kinds of do not know whether the true or false message emerged. Many students and friends in Wuhan and surrounding cities began to discuss the matter of returning tickets and staying behind.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Busy parents

I saw all the news, also persuade parents put on a mask in time, reduce the travel. At that time, I began to panic, not because I was worried that I might be infected when I went home, but because I was worried that I would be treated differently when I went back to Beijing. But I never wavered. I wanted to go home and spend the New Year with my parents.

We always have a family of three together at home to eat New Year's Eve Dinner, sit on the sofa to drink tea, eat snacks, grab red envelopes, watch the Spring Festival gala, this is a very common process, is the most important year-end ceremony of the family.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
There are no pedestrians downstairs in the community

In fact, I think very clearly, my health is very good, and I will be well protected, away from the crowd, always observe the health condition, to ensure their own health; if really unfortunate infection, I will go to the hospital as soon as possible, to avoid passing it on to anyone else.

But in front of the public opinion around me, I still feel like a traitor and a sinner. Whenever they talk about "Wuhan People" , I feel like they are accusing me. In their eyes, everyone who has been to Wuhan is a "virus bomb" that could erupt at any time. I can't tell if people are trying to dissuade me or they're trying to dissuade me. Fortunately, some of my friends have shown me some understanding.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Daddy who cooks

I arrived in Wuhan on the afternoon of the 22nd, and as soon as I woke up the next day, I received many messages from friends telling me that Wuhan was closed. I felt calm when I heard the news, because I was with my parents at the moment, instead of staying alone in Beijing, I could only understand the situation of my parents in the epidemic area from a distance.

I have a lot of friends stay away from home, they can only retweet some news, advised parents wear masks. But I can spend this "special" New Year with my parents and with each other.

On the eve of the Lunar New Year, my father set off for work.

My father is a freight station in Wuhan, a long time ago was scheduled to be on duty at the station on the night of New Year's Eve, and then on duty on the first day of the train, they called "sports car. ". So, New Year's Eve, the three of us in advance in the lunch to eat a reunion dinner, and then sent my father out to work.

Although Wuhan announced the closure of the city, the news of the suspension of specific freight trains did not come down until the evening of New Year's Eve. My mother and I were still a little worried. After all, we were not sure how many people would be on the train and whether there would be suspected patients. Luckily, my dad got the notice that the first day truck had stopped and he could go home after his shift.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The diary I kept during the SARS period

Because I grew up in Xiangyang, we do not have many relatives in Wuhan, had no plans to go out, so these two days is to stay at home, did not go anywhere.

This incident brought up the SARS period 17 years ago, but I don't remember much about it. So at home turned out the diary of a child, actually found the diary of the year. When SARS broke out in 2003, I was nine years old and in the third grade. At that time Hubei is not the disaster area, also did not suspend classes and so on, therefore does not have the deep impression. This time, the diary of that year, "SARS" did not feel too much impact on daily life, but even primary school students are aware of the "sars" , that the propaganda work at that time is still very good.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
This year's New Year's Eve, originally a family of three at home to eat New Year's Eve dinner, see the Spring Festival gala, now become I and my mother two people, each see the Spring Festival gala, grab the Red Envelope. But as long as you're with your family, New Year's Eve is always a good time. I had already prepared a red envelope for my parents and handed it to them at midnight.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Notice at the entrance of unit building

For now, I'm not particularly worried about getting infected because I and my family don't get out much. But some of the relatives are health care workers who have been working for a long time and are a little worried about their health. I saw the news, the overall epidemic situation should be very difficult, but my family and I as the epidemic area people, less travel, good protection, do not spread rumors and panic on the Internet, should be good we can do.

I wonder if the follow-up trip back to Beijing will be changed. Before I came back, I thought there might be some variables on the return trip, and I even packed two more books... so I'll wait and see. But still very worried about their return to Beijing, will be roommates, colleagues, and even some friends as a "source of infection" , avoid, after all, no symptoms do not mean not infected. Still many people will have "why do you want to go back to Wuhan, " such ideas, I can understand everyone's concerns, but I hope we can understand each other.

People across the country are expected to understand each other, not to say "Go Wuhan" and fire a map at the people of Wuhan. Expect life to return to normal as soon as possible, but it's going to be a long process.

Although the external environment is not safe,

But a family can be together every day

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
I'm in my 30s, and I'm at home looking at my phone.

Peixi, 30, freelance photographer, lives in the Panlongcheng Economic Development Zone

I am a freelance photographer from Shiyan, Hubei Province, and I run my own photography studio in Wuhan. 2020 was the first time I spent Chinese New Year in Wuhan. We moved to a new home in 2019, exactly the year before my family decided to spend Chinese New Year in Wuhan.

Unfortunately, as the disease got worse in Wuhan, the family came from Shiyan on January 20. On the same day, they had already seen the news that the disease seemed to be getting worse. They were worried, so they wore masks all the way on the high-speed train.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
I have a mask at home

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Vegetables and fruits that I have at home

On Jan. 23, the day the city was sealed off, I was horrified to see the news and to tell the truth, family members told each other to wear masks, wash their hands frequently and stay indoors. I was worried about the outbreak. Going to the supermarket felt like going to war. I was a little nervous about the crowds, even though most people were wearing masks.

Before the closure of the city I also took my mothers to the home near the supermarket chain, shopping malls. But on the day of the city closure, we were so scared that we didn't even dare to go out. I stayed at home and counted the materials placed on the balcony. Carrying it for 2 weeks was no problem.

New Year's Eve, lunch with family.

After the closure of the city, my family and I rarely go out, although the external environment is not safe, but our family can be together every day, eat the rich dishes made by my mother, feel very warm inside.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
On New Year's Eve, I am not in the mood to watch the Spring Festival gala. Although there are many stars I like in this year's Spring Festival gala, I am worried about the shortage of hospital materials and the poor allocation of resources to the white-clad soldiers in the front line.

This year I had a very anxious, very worried, feel very uncomfortable, New Year's Eve will be a lot of people's sleepless night, just hope that the next morning, there will be good news, Wuhan slowly getting better.
